description: DCAT distribution entries.
Local database identifier of the dataset.
Reference back to any catalogs that contain this item.
Reference back to any datasets that contain this item.
Reference back to any dataset series that contain this item.
Reference back to any datasets where this item functions as a sample.
A name given to the record.
A free-text account of the item.
An established standard to which the item conforms to.
A legal document under which the resource is made available.
A statement that concerns all rights not addressed with dct:license or dct:accessRights, such as copyright statements.
Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.
The rights described as an ODRL conformant policy.
Formal date of publication.
Most recent date of modification.
A data service that gives access to the distribution of the dataset.
A URL of the resource that gives access to a distribution of the dataset.
The URL of the downloadable file in a given format. The format is indicated by the distribution's dcterms:format and/or dcat:mediaType.
The size of a distribution in bytes.
The file format of the distribution. If using IANA type, use dcat:mediaType instead.
The compression format of the distribution in which the data is contained in a compressed form.
comment: DCAT Distribution / DCAT-AP-v3 Distribution: emphasizes IANA

description: The package format of the distribution in which one or more data files are grouped together.
comment: DCAT Distribution / DCAT-AP-v3 Distribution: emphasizes IANA

description: The media type of the distribution as defined by IANA.
Minimum spatial separation resolvable in a dataset, measured in meters.
Minimum time period resolvable in the dataset.
The legislation that mandates the creation or management of the Distribution.
An indication how long it is planned to keep the Distribution of the Dataset available.
The checksum belonging to the download URL retrievable data.
A page or document about this item.

A language of the item. This refers to the natural language used for textual metadata (i.e. titles, descriptions, etc) of a cataloged resource (i.e. dataset or service) or the textual values of a dataset distribution.
The status of this item.
This property must be attached to every entity that you wish the EJP-RD Virtual Platform to explore.
